About Us

Transforming Waste Into Opportunity

Our vision is to lead the global movement towards a zero-waste future. We aim to revolutionize waste management by integrating cutting-edge technology, fostering community partnerships and setting new standards for sustainability. Our goal is to minimize waste generation, maximize resource recovery and create a circular economy where waste becomes a valuable resource. By empowering communities and businesses alike, we envision a world where waste is no longer a problem, but an opportunity for innovation and growth. 

 

Together, we will build a cleaner, greener planet for generations to come.

​

Our mission is to provide innovative and sustainable waste management solutions that reduce environmental impact, optimize resource recovery and support the circular economy. We are committed to delivering exceptional service to our clients, ensuring compliance with regulations and fostering a culture of environmental responsibility. Through continuous improvement, collaboration, and the integration of cutting-edge technologies, we strive to protect our planet and create long-term value for our stakeholders, partners, communities and future generations.

10 Years of Being Hungry for Waste

Life at Hulladek

Looking for an Opportunity?

We believe in nurturing talent from within, creating opportunities for our employees to thrive and rise to leadership roles. Inclusivity, diversity and continuous learning are the pillars of our people-first approach.

Join our Team
LinkedIn

Nandan Mall, Founder & CMD of Hulladek Recycling incorporated this organization when he was only 23. Hulladek Recycling started as a college project when he was studying Bachelors of Commerce (BCom) at St. Xavier’s College, Kolkata.

​

At a young age, he understood the scenario of waste management in the country and the potential growth of this industry. His vision to revolutionize waste management in India has taken our organization from a start-up to a 100-crore organization with a team of 100 employees.


Collecting 25,000 Metric Tonnes of waste and impacting many lives, he has been recognised by several institutes for his entrepreneurship and leadership abilities. Some of them include Times Business Leader Award, Swacch Bharat Award and many more.
